The paper deals with human emotion recognition using RGBD video and face datasets, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. The proposed approach involves nonlinear mapping and neural networks, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of distance metrics and feature representations, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
